# TypeScript

- Strict mode is on. Do not loosen `tsconfig.json`.
- No `any`. Prefer `unknown` at boundaries, narrow with zod.
- Discriminated unions over class hierarchies. Always include a literal `type` / `kind` discriminator.
- All agent output is `AsyncIterable<AgentEvent>` — never `Promise<Reply>`.
- Async functions: always `await` or `return` a promise; no fire-and-forget without an explicit comment explaining why.
- Imports: external first, then internal (`@/`), then relative. No deep relative paths (`../../../`) — add a path alias instead.
- Errors: throw `Error` subclasses with structured `cause`. Never throw bare strings.
